The paper deals with inequalities satisfied by entropies, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT). The use of subspaces and ranks suggests a connection to linear algebra and discrete mathematics (cs.DS, cs.DM). The paper also mentions the Shannon inequalities, which are relevant to coding theory and communication (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of "general results" and the fact that there are "essentially new inequalities" beyond four variables suggests a connection to machine learning and statistical learning theory (cs.LG).
